Clicking on a page will collapse all by user expanded sibling nodes. This behaviour should be configurable. Many user find the automatic collapse really annoying.

If the workday in-app notification is disabled, the workday menu icon disappears but the placeholder remains. It should totally disappear.
!example.png!


h3. Workaround
Manually hide the notification box from the stylesheet (note: this does not work in Confluence Admin)
# Go to Confluence Admin >> Look and Feel >> Stylesheet >> Edit
# Add the following code and save
{code}
#notifications-anchor {
display:none;
}
{code}

h4. Steps to Reproduce
# Create a new space
# Add some pages
# Go to *Browse > Space Admin > Themes* and select Documentation Theme
# Customize the Documentation Theme by clicking "configure theme"
# Untick "Page tree" and add the following into the "Navigation" textbox:
{code}
{pagetree:expandCollapseAll=true}
{code}
# Save the configuration

h4. Expected Results
Pagetree is displayed with "Expand All" link shown correctly

h4. Actual Results
The "Expand All" link is cut off as per the following screenshot:
!screenshot012.jpg!

h4. Environment Information
Reproducible in 5.1.x using all browsers

h4. Workaround
Add the following CSS in *Space Admin > Stylesheet*:
{code}
#splitter-sidebar .plugin_pagetree {
margin-left: 0px !important;
}
{code}

