Hi guys,

It seems that Confluence does not allow you to insert a link into a page when you are using a mouse _right-click + paste_ instead of the keyboard shortcut.

Here's the process:
- On a Confluence page, select _Edit_;
- Type in the text that will become the link;
- Click _Link_ button in the toolbar;
- Then try to insert a link using the mouse _right-click + paste_.

When you paste this link, the _Insert_ button remains grayed out so you can't insert it.

If you edit or add a space to that link, then the _Insert_ button will be available.

If you use the keyboard shortcut keys, then no problem there.

Most likely this is related to the fact that Confluence is listening for keyboard keys and not mouse input.

Cheers,
Ricardo Martins

